{"title": "Recruiting Songs", "description": "This rousing collection of poems is sure to bring out patriotic sentiments in us all. These works were written with the glories of victory in mind - victory based on dignity and basic human rights for all. The strident call to arms expressed here can't help but stir the soul and inspire the imagination with thoughts of a vanquished enemy and the triumph of a defender of truth and liberty. <br><br>\r\n\r\nThe concept of hope, as elusive as it may be amid the field of battle, is always an asset when possessed by those in combat. This hope, this aspiration of a brighter future accompanied by a strident call to join the war effort is so aptly portrayed by poet Temple Scott. Here are a series of awe-inspiring songs of the splendor of victory, the anguish of defeat and, ultimately, the appeal to a higher power for guidance - in the words of Scott, \"Though tempest-tossed and battle-scarred, we still aspire Thy way to tread\". <br>\r\n - Summary by Bruce Kachuk", "duration": 1573, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "16890", "name": "Temple Scott"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/recruitingsongs_2205_librivox/recruiting_songs_2205.jpg", "copyright_year": "1917", "genres": ["Single author"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Bruce Kachuk"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Bruce Kachuk"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Rapunzelina"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Rapunzelina"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "The Call", "readers": [8786], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/recruitingsongs_2205_librivox/recruitingsongs_01_scott_64kb.mp3", "duration": 124}, {"section": 2, "title": "The Old Call", "readers": [8786], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/recruitingsongs_2205_librivox/recruitingsongs_02_scott_64kb.mp3", "duration": 149}, {"section": 3, "title": "Fight as Your Grandsires Fought", "readers": [8786], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/recruitingsongs